Description: tsagbug33860125.tsc - Test case for Bug 33860125

Test case for Bug 33860125
     Bring up RDBMS with sga_max_size=10G
     Once rdbms is up and has enough sga space, set:  alter system set "db_32k_cache_size"=1M;
     create two tablespaces, one with 8K block size (default) and 32K block size.

       create table temp(a int, b int, c int, d int, e int); and then insert dataâ¦
       create tablespace tbs32k  datafile '+DATAFILE/tbs32k.dbf' size 20M autoextend on blocksize 32K;
       create table test32k organization hybrid columnar compress for archive high tablespace tbs32k as select * from temp;
       create tablespace tbs8k  datafile '+DATAFILE/tbs8k.dbf' size 20M autoextend on blocksize 8K;
       create table test8k organization hybrid columnar compress for archive high tablespace tbs8k as select * from temp;

     Populate columnar cache for the 8K table.
     Once columnar cache for the 8K table is populated, run the following:

       alter system set "_kcfis_fast_response_enabled"=FALSE;
       select t8.a, count(distinct t32.a), count(*) from test32k t32 join (select a, b from test8k where a < 12345 and rownum <= 10) t8 on t32.b = t8.b group by  t8.a;

     Without the fix, you should see an oflsrv assert:  ORA-00600: internal error code, arguments: [PredicateOflDiskComn::addToBeFilteredIOSize::colc],
     With the fix, oflsrv should not fail.

