Description: tsagsiobjidzero.tsc - testcase for SI objid zero

SI should not be built when object id is zero.

Test steps:
       a. Setup Exadata
       b. Initialize columnar cache package for exadata feature validation in oratst
       c. Purge existing SI in cellcli - alter cell events = "immediate cellsrv.cellsrv_storidx(purge, ALL, 0, 0, 0)â
       d. Test write path
          a. Turn on new simulation event in cellcli - alter cell offloadgroupEvents="cellsrv_simevent[SI_OBJD_ZERO] frequency=1, count=20"
          b. Create a table and load some data
             create table t1 (col1 number, col2 date, col3 varchar2(2000), col4 nvarchar2(2000), col5 timestamp, col6 timestamp with time zone, col7 timestamp with local time zone, col8 float(20), col9 char(2000)) ;
             declare
             i NUMBER := 0 ;
             j NUMBER := 0 ;
             k timestamp:= systimestamp ;
             l nvarchar2(30):= 'stage' ;
             begin
                 for i in 1..30200 loop
                 insert into t1 values (i,sysdate+i,' storage',l || i,k + i,k + i,k + i,9999.99999+i, 'A') ;
                 commit ;
                 end loop ;
             end ;
             /
             commit ;
          c. Use checkCellStat to check cell stat - "nm_idx_not_built_objd_is_zero"
          d. Run cellsrvstat to check for one cell stat - "SI #idx not built objd zero"
       e. Purge existing SI in cellcli - alter cell events = "immediate cellsrv.cellsrv_storidx(purge, ALL, 0, 0, 0)â
       f. Test read path
          a.Turn on new simulation event in cellcli - alter cell offloadgroupEvents="cellsrv_simevent[SI_OBJD_ZERO] frequency=1, count=40"
          b.Attempt to build SI by reading from existing table - select count(*) from t1 where col1 < 0;
          c. Use checkCellStat to check cell stat - "nm_idx_not_built_objd_is_zero"
          d. Run cellsrvstat to check for one cell stat - "SI #idx not built objd zero"
       g. simevent turn off at the end of test

